President Obama has declared a state of emergency in New York due to the effects of Hurricane Sandy. This declaration authorizes the Department of Homeland Security and FEMA to coordinate relief efforts to help the local population and protect property and public health. FEMA is authorized to provide equipment and resources as needed and will provide 75 percent federal funding for emergency protective measures. Philip E. Parr has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area.